    "body": "Resolves #34670\n\nSince the switch to Python for Windows CI, the `qa-assets` files were not properly fetched during the test preparation phase, and the `DIR_UNIT_TEST_DATA` env variable was missing, causing `script_assets_tests` to skip or fail as a no-op on Windows test runners.\n\nThis PR adds the standard `urllib.request` retrieval to both `.github/ci-windows.py` and `.github/ci-windows-cross.py` during `prepare_tests` and sets `DIR_UNIT_TEST_DATA` in `run_unit_tests` and `run_tests` respectively to restore parity with the Bash pipelines.",
    "labels": [
      {
        "id": 62963516,
        "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2Mjk2MzUxNg==",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/labels/Tests",
        "name": "Tests",
